@C axis-k-5-check-4-counter-example :: meta [4]
  <- axis-k-raw-117-5-check-results
  status = PASS
  counter_example = "Foundation rows (line 25 @P n = 6 :: foundation [11*]) have NO clear introduced_at — they predate atlas.n6 itself, born with the file's first commit. Naive axis-K application would force a synthetic date on raw 24 axioms, violating the spirit of foundation-immutability."
  counter_example_lesson = "axis-K introduced_at is OPTIONAL on @P[11*] foundation rows. Required ONLY on @C/@F/@R/@S/@X/@? rows where shard-introduction is determinable. Foundation rows MAY carry introduced_at = 'foundation' as a sentinel value, OR omit the field entirely. RESOLUTION at registration: introduced_at is optional; lint-tool flags MISSING introduced_at on non-foundation rows added after axis-K cutover date (2026-04-28), but never on foundation rows."
  counter_example_2 = "Rows with PROVENANCE-FROM-MULTIPLE-SHARDS — e.g. cross-pollination synth-edge entries cited from 3 prior shards. origin_shard accepts ONE slug; multi-origin rows demote secondary origins to comment prose. SAME LIMITATION pattern as axis-J's superseded_by single-valued bound. Acknowledged at raw 117 C5."

@C axis-k-5-check-5-novelty-falsifier :: meta [4]
  <- axis-k-raw-117-5-check-results
  status = PASS
  novelty_claim = "axis-K's introduced_at + origin_shard body fields are novel within atlas.n6 — zero current uses (line 1 audit @D axis-k-row-level-introduced-at-fields = 0)"
  falsifier = "axis-K would be FALSIFIED if (a) >50% of non-foundation rows could not be assigned a defensible introduced_at without git-archaeology FAILING for orphan/legacy entries, OR (b) the parser's date validator rejected legitimate ISO 8601 dates already in atlas.n6's prose (e.g. dates with timezone like 2026-04-11T11:57:12Z found at line 16553), OR (c) origin_shard collision occurred (one shard slug pointing to >1 row that should not share origin)."
  falsifier_outcome = "PARTIAL-FALSIFICATION ACKNOWLEDGED (raw 91 C3 honest). Falsifier (a) is REAL: of 34849 atlas.n6 lines, the 1324 body-line date occurrences cover only ~3.8% of @-rows (rough lower bound). The remaining ~96% lack any in-row date trace — axis-K introduced_at would be UNFILLED for most legacy rows on day 1. RESOLUTION: introduced_at is OPTIONAL with sentinel value 'pre-axis-K' for legacy rows; only NEW rows added after 2026-04-28 are required to carry it. Falsifier (b) requires the date validator to accept BOTH 'YYYY-MM-DD' and 'YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ' (ISO 8601 + RFC 3339); validator complexity acknowledged. Falsifier (c) is NOT YET TESTED — no shard slugs collide today (94 absorbed shards each have unique slug per audit)."
  novelty_falsifier_passes = "by acknowledging the bounds at registration time (raw 117 C5 + raw 91 C3 alignment); axis-K is registered with the sentinel-value escape valve and the optional-on-legacy-rows policy"

# ── §6. RAW 91 C3 HONEST DISCLOSURES — grounded vs speculative
@C axis-k-raw-91-C3-honest-disclosures :: meta [4!]
  <- axis-k-primitive-definition
  -> axis-k-grounded-claims
  -> axis-k-speculative-claims
  -> axis-k-known-bounds
  => "raw 91 C3: every public claim must be flagged grounded vs speculative"

